AI-Powered Test Case Generation Skill — Implementation Tasks (Phase 1 MVP)

Version: 1.0
Date: 2026-06-04
Status: Ready for Implementation

==============================================================================
MVP RULE: OPTIONAL OPENAPI SUPPORT
==============================================================================

OpenAPI Support (CONDITIONAL):
  - OpenAPI input is OPTIONAL.
  - System must work with only User Stories and Acceptance Criteria.
  - If OpenAPI is provided → generate API Contract Tests (and API coverage metrics).
  - If OpenAPI is absent → skip API Contract Analyzer and Contract Test Generation.
  - Generate Functional Tests, Validation Tests, Boundary Tests, Gherkin, Playwright,
    Traceability Matrix, and Coverage Reports regardless of OpenAPI availability.
  - Manifest includes `openApiIncluded: boolean` flag.
  - Coverage report adapts based on whether OpenAPI was processed.

==============================================================================
TASK EXECUTION ORDER & DEPENDENCIES
==============================================================================

Execution sequence (critical path):
  Week 1: CORE-001 → CORE-006 (foundation)
  Week 2: REQ-001 → REQ-005 (REQUIRED); API-001 → API-005 (OPTIONAL, parallel)
  Week 3: DESIGN-001 → DESIGN-006, DATA-001 → DATA-005 (generation)
  Week 4: GHERKIN-001 → GHERKIN-005, PLAYWRIGHT-001 → PLAYWRIGHT-005 (adapters, parallel),
          TRACE-001, COVERAGE-001, ASSEMBLE-001, ASSEMBLE-002 (assembly)

Dependency graph:
  CORE-* ────────┬──→ REQ-* (REQUIRED) ──┬──→ DESIGN-* ──→ DATA-* ──┬──→ GHERKIN-*
                 │                       │  (optional API input)    │
                 ├──→ API-* (OPTIONAL) ──┘                          ├──→ PLAYWRIGHT-*
                 │                                                   │
                 └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┼──→ TRACE-*
                                                                     │
                                                                     └──→ COVERAGE-*
                                                                          ASSEMBLE-*

==============================================================================
WEEK 1: CORE INFRASTRUCTURE
==============================================================================

CORE-001: Implement core data model (dataclasses)
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Create Python dataclasses for all core types used throughout the generator.
    Focus on immutability and clear field definitions with type hints.
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Create src/core/model.py with:
        - Requirement (id, text, type, actor, source, business_rules, etc.)
        - ApiSpec (source, title, endpoints)
        - Endpoint (path, method, summary, request, responses)
        - RequestSchema (required, schema)
        - Response (status, description, schema)
        - JsonSchema (type, format, properties, required, constraints)
        - Constraint (field, type, rules)
        - TestCase (id, sourceIds, description, intent, type, request_example, etc.)
        - Fixture (test_case_id, request_payload, expected_response, headers)
        - TraceabilityRecord (requirement_id, test_case_id, artifact_path, rationale)
        - CoverageReport (metrics)
        - GenerationManifest (version, timestamp, seed, sources, test_cases, artifacts)
    1.2 Verify all type hints are correct
    1.3 Add __repr__ methods for debugging
  
  Dependencies: None
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ All 12+ dataclasses defined with correct fields and types
    ✓ Imports work without external dependencies (stdlib only)
    ✓ Model can be instantiated and serialized to/from JSON
  
  Estimated Effort: 2 hours
  Priority: P0 (blocker)

---

CORE-002: Implement canonicalization & deterministic hashing
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Build deterministic SHA256-based canonicalization for sources.
    Ensure identical inputs always produce identical hashes.
  
  Subtasks:
    2.1 Create src/core/canonicalize.py with:
        - canonicalize_json(dict) → str (sorted keys, stable format)
        - canonicalize_text(str) → str (strip whitespace, normalize line endings)
        - compute_checksum(content) → str (SHA256 hex)
        - compute_deterministic_seed(sources: Dict[str, str]) → str
    2.2 Add tests for edge cases (empty dict, unicode, special chars)
    2.3 Verify determinism: run same function 100x, same hash
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Canonicalization is deterministic (identical output for identical input)
    ✓ Checksum function produces valid SHA256 hex strings
    ✓ Seed changes when any source file changes
    ✓ Seed remains stable when run order changes (content-based, not order-based)
  
  Estimated Effort: 3 hours
  Priority: P0 (blocker)

---

CORE-003: Implement simple YAML/JSON loader (no external deps)
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Create a minimal YAML parser using only stdlib.
    Must parse OpenAPI specs, validation rules, and config files.
    Already partially implemented in speckit_generator.py; refactor into src/core/
  
  Subtasks:
    3.1 Create src/core/loaders.py with:
        - _parse_scalar(value: str) → Any (string, int, float, bool, list)
        - _build_container_stack(lines: List[str]) → Dict (YAML parsing)
        - load_yaml_or_json(path: Path) → Dict (auto-detect format)
    3.2 Test against:
        - config.yaml
        - examples/api-spec.yaml
        - examples/validation-rules.yaml
    3.3 Handle edge cases:
        - quoted strings ("key": "value")
        - nested lists and dicts
        - comments and blank lines
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Parses valid YAML/JSON without external libs
    ✓ Handles quoted keys/values correctly
    ✓ Produces valid Python dicts (no dangling references)
    ✓ All sample files parse correctly
    ✓ Error handling for malformed input
  
  Estimated Effort: 2 hours
  Priority: P0 (blocker)

