CORE-005: Implement manifest generation & validation
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Build manifest.json generation and validation logic.
    Manifest tracks determinism, source checksums, and artifact paths.
  
  Subtasks:
    5.1 Create src/core/manifest.py with:
        - build_manifest(sources: Dict, test_cases: List, artifacts: List) → GenerationManifest
        - validate_manifest(manifest) → bool (all required fields present)
        - validate_checksums(manifest, actual_files) → List[str] (mismatches)
    5.2 Manifest must include:
        - generator_version (e.g., "0.1.0")
        - generated_at (ISO 8601 timestamp)
        - deterministic_seed (SHA256 of sources)
        - sources: { path, checksum }[]
        - test_cases: { id, source_ids, checksum }[]
        - artifacts: { path, type, checksum }[]
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, CORE-002
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Manifest is valid JSON when serialized
    ✓ Deterministic seed matches input sources
    ✓ All source/artifact paths are relative or absolute (consistent)
    ✓ Validation catches missing required fields
    ✓ Checksum validation detects file tampering
  
  Estimated Effort: 2 hours
  Priority: P0

