==============================================================================
WEEK 2: PARSERS
==============================================================================

REQ-001: Implement Requirement Analyzer (markdown parser)
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Parse markdown user stories and extract acceptance criteria.
    Format: "As a <actor>, I want <action>, so <benefit>."
            "## Acceptance Criteria
             - AC-NNN: <criterion>"
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Create src/parsers/markdown.py with:
        - parse_markdown_story(path: Path) → Requirement[]
        - extract_actor(text: str) → str (regex: "As a ([^,]+)")
        - extract_acceptance_criteria(text: str) → Requirement[]
        - extract_business_rules(text: str) → str[]
        - extract_preconditions(text: str) → str[]
        - extract_postconditions(text: str) → str[]
        - normalize_requirement_id(text: str) → str (AC-001 or generate REQ-HASH)
    1.2 Parsing rules:
        - Recognize "## Acceptance Criteria" section
        - Parse "- AC-NNN: <text>" or "- <text>"
        - Extract actor from "As a <actor>" pattern
        - Detect business rules ("must", "should", "only", "requires")
        - Detect preconditions ("Given", "when", "if")
        - Detect postconditions ("Then", "should", "result", "returns")
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, CORE-003
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Parses examples/user-story.md correctly
    ✓ Extracts all 4 acceptance criteria
    ✓ Identifies actor as "registered user"
    ✓ Handles IDs (AC-001, AC-002, etc.)
    ✓ Generates REQ-HASH for missing IDs
    ✓ Returns Requirement[] with all fields populated
  
  Estimated Effort: 3 hours
  Priority: P0

---

REQ-002: Implement API Contract Analyzer (OpenAPI parser)
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Parse OpenAPI 3.x specs and extract endpoints, schemas, constraints.
    Handle $ref dereferencing, extract field constraints from JSON Schema.
  
  Subtasks:
    2.1 Create src/parsers/openapi.py with:
        - parse_openapi(path: Path) → ApiSpec
        - extract_endpoints(spec: Dict) → Endpoint[]
        - dereference_schema(schema: Dict, spec: Dict) → Dict (resolve $ref)
        - extract_field_constraints(schema: Dict) → Constraint[]
        - normalize_status_code(code: str) → int
    2.2 Extract from OpenAPI:
        - Info: title, version
        - Paths: path, method (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)
        - RequestBody: required, schema, content-type
        - Responses: status code, description, schema, content-type
    2.3 Constraint extraction from JsonSchema:
        - type, format, minLength, maxLength, minimum, maximum, enum, pattern
        - required array (list of required field names)
    2.4 Handle:
        - Simple schemas (inline)
        - Referenced schemas ($ref)
        - Nested objects and arrays
        - AllOf, anyOf, oneOf (log as TODO)
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, CORE-003
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Parses examples/api-spec.yaml correctly
    ✓ Extracts 1 endpoint (POST /api/users)
    ✓ Extracts request schema with 3 properties (email, password, age)
    ✓ Extracts 3 responses (201, 400, 409)
    ✓ Extracts constraints: email format, password minLength, age minimum
    ✓ Dereferences $ref (if present in test fixture)
    ✓ Returns ApiSpec with all fields populated
  
  Estimated Effort: 4 hours
  Priority: P0

---

REQ-003: Implement Validation Rule Analyzer
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Parse validation rules from YAML (custom format).
    Map field constraints and validation messages.
  
  Subtasks:
    3.1 Create src/parsers/validation.py with:
        - parse_validation_rules(path: Path) → Constraint[]
        - extract_rules(data: Dict) → Constraint[]
        - normalize_rule(rule: Dict) → Constraint
    3.2 Input format:
        validation_rules:
          - id: VR-001
            field: email
            rule: required
            message: Email is required...
          - id: VR-002
            field: password
            rule: required
            ...
    3.3 Output: Constraint[] with field, type, rules dict
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, CORE-003
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Parses examples/validation-rules.yaml correctly
    ✓ Extracts 3 rules (email required, password required, age minimum)
    ✓ Maps field names correctly
    ✓ Populates Constraint[] with all required fields
  
  Estimated Effort: 2 hours
  Priority: P1

---

