        - parse_openapi(path: Path | None) → ApiSpec | None
        - extract_endpoints(spec: Dict) → Endpoint[]
        - dereference_schema(schema: Dict, spec: Dict) → Dict (resolve $ref)
        - extract_field_constraints(schema: Dict) → Constraint[]
        - normalize_status_code(code: str) → int
    1.2 Extract from OpenAPI:
        - Info: title, version
        - Paths: path, method (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)
        - RequestBody: required, schema, content-type
        - Responses: status code, description, schema, content-type
    1.3 Constraint extraction from JsonSchema:
        - type, format, minLength, maxLength, minimum, maximum, enum, pattern
        - required array (list of required field names)
    1.4 Handle:
        - Simple schemas (inline)
        - Referenced schemas ($ref)
        - Nested objects and arrays
        - AllOf, anyOf, oneOf (log as TODO)
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, CORE-003
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Parses examples/api-spec.yaml correctly (when provided)
    ✓ Extracts 1 endpoint (POST /api/users)
    ✓ Extracts request schema with 3 properties (email, password, age)
    ✓ Extracts 3 responses (201, 400, 409)
    ✓ Extracts constraints: email format, password minLength, age minimum
    ✓ Dereferences $ref (if present in test fixture)
    ✓ Returns ApiSpec with all fields populated
    ✓ [CONDITIONAL] Gracefully returns None if openapi_path is missing or file not found
    ✓ No exception thrown if OpenAPI component is disabled in config
  
  Estimated Effort: 4 hours
  Priority: P1 (optional track)

