==============================================================================
WEEK 3: GENERATORS (CORE)
==============================================================================

DESIGN-001: Implement Test Design Generator
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Generate test cases from requirements, optional API specs, and constraints.
    For each acceptance criterion: 1 positive, 1 negative, 1 boundary test.
    For each constraint: 1 validation test.
    [CONDITIONAL] For each response code (if OpenAPI provided): 1 contract test.
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Create src/generators/test_design.py with:
        - generate_test_cases(requirements, [optional] api_spec, constraints) → TestCase[]
        - generate_positive_test(requirement, [optional] endpoint) → TestCase
        - generate_negative_test(requirement, constraint) → TestCase
        - generate_boundary_test(requirement, constraint) → TestCase
        - generate_validation_test(constraint, [optional] endpoint) → TestCase
        - generate_contract_test(endpoint, response) → TestCase [CONDITIONAL]
        - deduplicate_tests(tests) → TestCase[] (normalized key hash)
    1.2 Test case ID format: TC-<REQ-ID>-<INTENT>
        - TC-AC-001-POS (positive) [ALWAYS]
        - TC-AC-001-NEG (negative) [ALWAYS]
        - TC-AC-001-BOUNDARY (boundary) [ALWAYS]
        - TC-VR-001-VALIDATION (validation) [ALWAYS]
        - TC-<HASH>-CONTRACT (contract) [CONDITIONAL: only if OpenAPI provided]
    1.3 For each test:
        - Assign sourceIds[] (which requirements it covers)
        - Write rationale (why this test matters)
        - Assign intent (positive, negative, boundary, validation, contract[optional])
        - Assign type (functional, validation, api[optional], boundary)
        - Include tags[] for filtering
    1.4 Handle missing OpenAPI:
        - If api_spec is None: skip contract test generation
        - Still generate validation tests from acceptance criteria constraints
        - Include note in test rationale if contract test would have been generated
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, REQ-001, API-001 (optional)
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Generates 3 tests per acceptance criterion (POS, NEG, BOUNDARY) [ALWAYS]
    ✓ Generates 1 test per constraint [ALWAYS]
    ✓ [CONDITIONAL] Generates 1 test per response code (if OpenAPI provided)
    ✓ [CONDITIONAL] Skips contract tests gracefully if OpenAPI is None
    ✓ Test IDs are unique and deterministic
    ✓ Each test has sourceIds and rationale
    ✓ Duplicate detection works (hash-based)
    ✓ Sample input with OpenAPI (4 ACs, 1 endpoint, 3 constraints) produces ~15 tests
    ✓ Sample input without OpenAPI (4 ACs, 3 constraints) produces ~12 tests (no contracts)
  
  Estimated Effort: 5 hours
  Priority: P0

