DATA-001: Implement Test Data Generator (mock data)
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Generate constraint-driven mock payloads for test cases.
    For positive tests: valid data.
    For negative tests: violate one constraint.
    For boundary tests: edge values.
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Create src/generators/test_data.py with:
        - generate_mock_payload(schema, intent, seed) → Dict
        - generate_mock_value(field_def, constraint, intent, seed) → Any
        - generate_fixtures(test_cases, seed) → Fixture[]
    1.2 Constraint-driven generation:
        - string: use format (email, uuid), minLength, maxLength, pattern, enum
        - integer: use minimum, maximum, enum
        - boolean: true/false
        - array: empty or 1-2 items
        - object: recursive descent
    1.3 Deterministic PRNG:
        - Seed from deterministicSeed (manifest)
        - Same seed → identical mock values
        - Different seeds → different values
    1.4 Intent-based behavior:
        - positive: satisfy all constraints
        - negative: violate exactly one constraint
        - boundary: use min-1, max+1, empty string, etc.
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, CORE-002, DESIGN-001
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Generates valid positive payloads (match all constraints)
    ✓ Generates invalid negative payloads (violate one constraint)
    ✓ Generates boundary payloads (edge values)
    ✓ Deterministic PRNG: same seed → identical values
    ✓ Handles email format, minLength, minimum, enum correctly
    ✓ Fixtures include request, expected_response (if available), headers
  
  Estimated Effort: 5 hours
  Priority: P0

---

