==============================================================================
WEEK 4: ADAPTERS & ASSEMBLY
==============================================================================

GHERKIN-001: Implement Gherkin Generator
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Render Gherkin scenarios from test cases.
    Format: Feature, Scenario, Given/When/Then steps.
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Create src/adapters/gherkin.py with:
        - render_gherkin(test_cases, output_dir) → None
        - generate_scenario(test_case) → str
        - generate_given_steps(test_case) → str[]
        - generate_when_steps(test_case) → str[]
        - generate_then_steps(test_case) → str[]
    1.2 Template structure:
        Feature: Generated acceptance and API tests
          @positive
          Scenario: TC-AC-001-POS - Positive test for '...'
            Given a user has a positive payload
            When the client submits a POST request to /api/users
            Then the response status should be 201
            And the response body should match the expected schema
    1.3 Generate:
        - Feature file with all scenarios
        - Tags for intent (@positive, @negative, @boundary, @contract)
        - Deterministic order (sorted by test case ID)
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, DESIGN-001, DATA-001
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Generates valid Gherkin syntax (can parse with gherkin-parser)
    ✓ All test cases rendered as scenarios
    ✓ Correct Given/When/Then structure
    ✓ Tags included (@positive, @negative, etc.)
    ✓ Output file: gherkin/generated_tests.feature
    ✓ Deterministic (same seed → identical feature file)
  
