PLAYWRIGHT-001: Implement Playwright Generator
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Render TypeScript Playwright test skeletons.
    Include HTTP request/response, assertions (with TODOs).
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Create src/adapters/playwright.py with:
        - render_playwright(test_cases, output_dir) → None
        - generate_test_function(test_case) → str
        - generate_request_block(test_case) → str
        - generate_assertion_block(test_case) → str
        - generate_fixture_import(test_case) → str
    1.2 Template structure:
        import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
        
        test('TC-AC-001-POS - Positive test', async ({ request }) => {
          const payload = { email: "user@example.com", password: "Password123", age: 18 };
          const response = await request.post('/api/users', { data: payload });
          expect(response.status()).toBe(201);
          const body = await response.json();
          expect(body).toBeTruthy();
          // TODO: add field-level assertions and response schema validation
        });
    1.3 Generate:
        - One .spec.ts file per test case or all in one (configurable)
        - Deterministic file naming: TC-<ID>.spec.ts
        - Include fixture references
        - TODO comments for manual completion
  
  Dependencies: CORE-001, DESIGN-001, DATA-001
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ Generates valid TypeScript syntax (can compile with tsc)
    ✓ All test cases rendered as test() blocks
    ✓ Correct HTTP method, endpoint, headers
    ✓ Payload matches mock data generated
    ✓ Assertions include status code + TODO for schema
    ✓ Output files: playwright/*.spec.ts
    ✓ Deterministic (same seed → identical TS files)
  
  Estimated Effort: 4 hours
  Priority: P0

