ASSEMBLE-001: Wire up end-to-end flow in run_generation.py
  Type: Implementation
  Description:
    Update run_generation.py to orchestrate all components.
    Load config → conditionally parse inputs → generate tests → render output → validate.
  
  Subtasks:
    1.1 Update run_generation.py to:
        1. Load config.yaml
        2. Parse REQUIRED inputs (requirements from markdown)
        3. [CONDITIONAL] Parse optional inputs (OpenAPI spec if openapi_path provided)
        4. [CONDITIONAL] Parse optional validation rules (if validation_rules_path provided)
        5. Generate test cases (passes None for api_spec if not provided)
        6. Generate mock data
        7. Render Gherkin, Playwright
        8. Build traceability matrix, coverage report (adapted for optional API), gaps report
        9. Generate manifest (includes openApiIncluded flag)
        10. Validate 100% coverage of applicable metrics (skip API coverage if openapi_path missing)
        11. Write all artifacts to output/<timestamp>/
    1.2 Error handling:
        - Missing markdown file → ERROR (fail fast)
        - Missing OpenAPI file → LOG WARNING, set api_spec=None, continue
        - Missing validation rules → LOG WARNING, set constraints=[], continue
        - Parse errors → log as gaps, continue
        - Invalid output → raise error
    1.3 Conditional logic:
        - Check config.openapi_path existence and readability
        - Skip API-related parsing/generation if not provided
        - Adapt coverage validation based on what was provided
    1.4 Logging:
        - Progress messages (parsing, generating, rendering)
        - Flag when optional inputs are skipped: "OpenAPI not provided; skipping API contract tests"
        - Summary statistics (test count, coverage % for each metric)
        - Execution time
  
  Dependencies: All previous components (CORE-*, REQ-*, API-* [optional], DESIGN-*, DATA-*,
                GHERKIN-*, PLAYWRIGHT-*, TRACE-*, COVERAGE-*)
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ End-to-end execution without errors
    ✓ All required artifacts generated (gherkin/, playwright/, *.json files)
    ✓ Output structure matches plan
    ✓ Manifest includes openApiIncluded flag and all required fields
    ✓ Log messages are clear and helpful (especially when skipping optional components)
    ✓ Execution time < 5 seconds
    ✓ [WITH OpenAPI] Generates API contract tests and API coverage metrics
    ✓ [WITHOUT OpenAPI] Generates functional/validation/boundary tests only; coverage report omits API metrics
    ✓ Coverage validation succeeds (100% of applicable metrics)
  
  Estimated Effort: 3 hours
  Priority: P0

---

ASSEMBLE-002: End-to-end integration tests
  Type: Integration Test
  Description:
    Full flow tests: specification → artifacts.
    Test both WITH and WITHOUT OpenAPI to verify conditional behavior.
  
  Test Scenarios:
    [SCENARIO 1 - WITH OpenAPI]
    - Full flow: markdown + OpenAPI + validation rules → all outputs
    - Includes: Functional, Validation, Boundary, Contract tests
    - Coverage: 100% acceptance, validation, API coverage
    - Manifest: openApiIncluded=true, apiCoverage populated
    
    [SCENARIO 2 - WITHOUT OpenAPI]
    - Partial flow: markdown + validation rules (no OpenAPI) → outputs without API tests
    - Includes: Functional, Validation, Boundary tests (no Contract)
    - Coverage: 100% acceptance, validation (API coverage skipped)
    - Manifest: openApiIncluded=false, apiCoverage null/omitted
    
    [SCENARIO 3 - MINIMAL]
    - Minimal flow: markdown only (no OpenAPI, no validation rules)
    - Includes: Functional, Validation tests (from AC constraints)
    - Coverage: 100% acceptance, (validation from AC-derived constraints)
    - Manifest: openApiIncluded=false
    
    [ALL SCENARIOS]
    - Determinism: run twice, compare checksums (manifest)
    - Traceability: every test → at least 1 requirement
    - Anti-hallucination: no invented fields/endpoints
  
  Test Fixtures:
    - tests/fixtures/sample_spec/ (markdown, OpenAPI, validation rules)
    - tests/fixtures/sample_spec_minimal/ (markdown only)
    - tests/fixtures/expected_output/ (reference outputs for each scenario)
  
  Dependencies: ASSEMBLE-001
  Acceptance Criteria:
    ✓ [WITH OpenAPI] Full flow completes with all outputs and API tests
    ✓ [WITHOUT OpenAPI] Flow completes gracefully, skipping API tests and coverage
    ✓ [MINIMAL] Flow completes with markdown only
    ✓ All output artifacts generated and valid (for their scenario)
    ✓ Deterministic (run twice → identical checksums)
    ✓ 100% coverage (for applicable metrics in each scenario)
    ✓ Traceability complete
    ✓ No hallucinated content (especially no invented API endpoints when OpenAPI missing)
    ✓ Manifest validates for each scenario (openApiIncluded flag matches reality)
    ✓ Coverage report includes/omits apiCoverage based on scenario
  
  Estimated Effort: 4 hours
  Priority: P0

